<p>If I load an image file with a resolution higher of 64x64, than I set it to fullscreen mode, the cursor becomes hidden. But, if I try to click in to second screen, the application go to in the "backbuffer" and cursors returns, while I don't click to application.</p>  <p>Does anyone know why this is happening?</p>  <p>Here is my code:</p>  <pre><code>Gdiplus::Bitmap* image = Gdiplus::Bitmap::FromFile( ws.c_str() );   HBITMAP bmp;         image-&gt;GetHBITMAP( Gdiplus::Color::Black, &amp;bmp );  HBITMAP bmpm;         image-&gt;GetHBITMAP( Gdiplus::Color::Black, &amp;bmpm );  ICONINFO iconInfo; iconInfo.fIcon = FALSE;  iconInfo.hbmColor = bmp;  iconInfo.hbmMask = bmpm;  iconInfo.xHotspot = xhot;  iconInfo.yHotspot = yhot;  HICON ico = CreateIconIndirect(&amp;iconInfo);  cd.m_Icons.push_back( ico );                       delete image;  (( SDL_CursorEx * )cd.m_Cursor)-&gt;driverdata = cd.m_Icons[ curFrame ];  SDL_SetCursor( cd.m_Cursor ); </code></pre>